thanks
Homonym Number:
Word Class: exclamation
Sense Number:
Definition:for `please' or `thank(ing) you in anticipation' in usu. shopping contexts as, e.g. shop-person to customer, when a finalisation of a transaction is anticipated: `That will be $1.99 thanks.'
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: 1987 Dec p.c. Professor G.E. Hughes (Wellington) `Noticed over the years, and reminded again recently, that this seems a NZ usage or idiom as distinct from British usage.'
